<br>
As I've stated from the begining what I posted was based on what has been said in this thread.  My conclusions were drawn from the same information.  I.E. - what was posted here.  I wasn't there.  I had no input with what occurred.  I only know what I saw posted here.  And the one thing that bothered me were the inconsistencies between what Trist posted and what other Radiant members posted.  I know none of the reputations of any of the people involved other than Trist.  <br>
<br>
I'm not a raid expert by ANY means.  In fact I'm nothing more than a wannabe raider.  Been to Fear once.  Been to POA twice.  Done Kael.  Done Chardok.  That's it.  So again, my conclusions were based only on what I read here.  When someone says they trained the whole temple fast and kited the mobs, that's what it meant to me.  Nothing more and nothing less.  When someone states later that they didn't train someone, I wonder how the train that they had earlier, got to the group that was trained.  <br>
<br>
I had no knowledge that training is a tactic in Fear as I have no expertise in it.  I made my conclusions based on what I read...the facts as they were presented here, and they may not even be facts.<br>
<br>
So while I can be flamed for my conclusions, they weren't based on bias, only on my limited knowledge of Fear and the words that were posted here.  And dueling &quot;to clear my conscience&quot; was certainly not my motivating factor.  It just seemed like a fun way to bring it to a closure.  Hell Bane already offered to do what is right so it will be resolved as he seems very honorable to me.<br>
<br>
